title.narrative: MNCH, ADOLESCENT HEALTH

description.narrative: Central and decentralized health authorities in targeted areas have improved capacity to roll-out and sustain MHCH, STI/HIV prevention and adolescent mental health services, through established subnational delivery systems., which contributes to Adolescents And Hiv/Aids, Climate Change, Disaster Risks And Envionmental Degradation, Cross Sectoral - Gender Discriminatory Roles And Practices, Cross Sectoral - Gender Discriminatory Roles And Practices (Covid), Fast-Track The End Of Hiv/Aids, Health And Development In Early Childhood And Adolescence, Health Systems Strengthening, Health â€“ General, Immunization Services As Part Of Primary Health Care, Immunization Services As Part Of Primary Health Care (Covid), Maternal And Newborn Health, Mental Health And Psychosocial Well-Being, Nutrition Of Adolescents And Women, Polio Eradication, Strengthening Primary Health Care And High-Impact Health Interventions, Strengthening Primary Health Care And High-Impact Health Interventions (Covid). UNICEF aims to achieve this through Advocacy And Communications, Advocacy And Public Engagement, Community Engagement, Social And Behaviour Change, Data, Research, Evaluation And Knowledge Management, Evaluations, Research And Data, Fostering Innovation And Use Of New Technologies, Innovation, Operational Support To Programme Delivery, Systems Strengthening And Institution Building, Systems Strengthening To Leave No One Behind. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: By 2021, the most disadvantaged children in Mongolia benefit from increased access to and utilization of services that promote health and nutrition, including Water, Sanitation, and Hygiene (WASH) and interventions that mitigate the impact of air pollution on child survival.
